Prevent emacsclient from launching the user's alternate editor.

An MCP transport must fail when its selected Emacs socket is unavailable.
Falling back to an interactive editor turns readiness probes into false
successes and may hang while a JSON-RPC expression is opened as a filename.

--- a/anvil-stdio.sh
+++ b/anvil-stdio.sh
@@ -20 +20,5 @@
-
+
+# A transport failure must remain a failure.  In particular, never let
+# emacsclient reinterpret an Elisp expression as a file for another editor.
+unset ALTERNATE_EDITOR
+
